-- Chrysler U.S. strike to shut Windsor plant: CAW
-- 
-- Wed Oct 10, 2007 12:14pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/10/us-chrysler-canada-layoffs-idUSTOR00214620071010

 

 TORONTO  (Reuters) - Automaker Chrysler's Windsor, Ontario, minivan plant, which employs 5,400 people, is to shut down by 3 p.m. (1900 GMT) on Wednesday due to a strike at some of Chrysler's U.S. plants, Buzz Hargrove, president of the Canadian Auto Workers union said. 

 Chrysler's Brampton, Ontario, assembly plant, which produces the company's 300 series of cars and employs 4,000 people will shut down by Thursday afternoon, Hargrove said.